properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 4 at 5:11AM EST until January 5 at 1:00PM EST by NWS Mount Holly NJ
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northwest winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts up to 40 kt and
seas 4 to 7 feet expected.

* WHERE...The Atlantic coastal waters adjacent to New Jersey and
Delaware.

* WHEN...From midnight tonight to 1 PM EST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 1 PM EST SUNDAY
